article.headline: Air Force 68, Charleston Southern 58
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Grant Parker led all players with 25 points and a career-high 11 rebounds as Air Force defeated Charleston Southern 68-58 Saturday night. Parker's double-double was the first of his career. Tom Fow added 13 points for the Falcons (3-1). Jamarco Warren led the Buccaneers (3-2) with 18 points, and Kelvin Martin had 14 points and nine rebounds. Charleston Southern led 22-13 with 7:56 remaining in the first half before Air Force took control with a pair of big runs. The Falcons closed the first half with a 15-2 run to take a 28-26 advantage at intermission, then opened the second half with a 20-8 outburst. Air Force was without starting center Sammy Schafer and reserve forward Taylor Broekhuis, who were both sidelined with injuries.
